  "body": "I was looking for codes where the variables should be `const` but set as `var`.\r\n\r\nFor example, this code in `big.go` : \r\n```\r\nvar (\r\n\tBig1   = big.NewInt(1)\r\n\tBig2   = big.NewInt(2)\r\n\tBig3   = big.NewInt(3)\r\n\tBig0   = big.NewInt(0)\r\n\tBig32  = big.NewInt(32)\r\n\tBig256 = big.NewInt(256)\r\n\tBig257 = big.NewInt(257)\r\n)\r\n```\r\n\r\nCalling `Set`, `Neg`, `Add`  on these variables could change the values.\r\n```\r\nfunc TestSet(t *testing.T) {\r\n\tx := Big1\r\n\tx.Set(big.NewInt(3))\r\n\r\n\tfmt.Println(Big1) // this prints 3\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunc TestNeg(t *testing.T) {\r\n\tx := Big1\r\n\tx.Neg(big.NewInt(3))\r\n\r\n\tfmt.Println(Big1) // this prints -3\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunc TestAdd(t *testing.T) {\r\n\tx := Big1\r\n\tx.Add(x, big.NewInt(5))\r\n\r\n\tfmt.Println(Big1) // this prints 6\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis could effect the whole project if such code exist : \r\n```\r\n\tbalance := stateDB.GetBalance(receiver) // this results in common.Big0 if receiver does not exist\r\n\tbalance.Add(balance, amount)            // this could change the value of common.Big0\r\n```\r\n\r\nShouldn't these codes be defined as get functions instead of `var`s? For example,\r\n```\r\nfunc Big1() *big.Int { return big.NewInt(1) }\r\nfunc Big2() *big.Int { return big.NewInt(2) }\r\nfunc Big3() *big.Int { return big.NewInt(3) }\r\n..\r\n```",
